def: Practicing or exhibiting coquetry; alluring; enticing.A pretty, coquettish housemaid. W. Irving.
A loding room; esp., a sleeping place partitioned off from alarge dormitory.
The quality of being aged; oldness.Custom without truth is but agedness of error. Milton.
The quality or state of being touchy peevishness; irritability;irascibility.
To adorn. [Obs.]Congealed little drops which do the morn adore. Spenser.
One who, or that which, warms.
The office or work of an observer.
One who uses tautological words or phrases.
